WEBVTT

00:02.850 --> 00:05.476
You are listening to a teaching from Reality LA.

00:08.544 --> 00:09.185
My name is Jonathan.

00:09.245 --> 00:11.732
If I haven't met you before, I'd love to meet you after the gathering.

00:11.752 --> 00:16.082
As was said earlier, we're currently in a four week sermon series

00:16.194 --> 00:19.597
talking about the essentials of church involvement.

00:19.617 --> 00:29.806
And while there are a number of ways you can be involved here at Reality LA, we wanna spend some time this year giving a little bit of clarity and even motivation for what matters the most.

00:30.627 --> 00:40.475
And so if you weren't here a couple weeks ago on Vision Sunday, I would encourage you to go and listen to that sermon, laying out kind of how the elders and leadership of the church senses God leading us this year.

00:41.176 --> 00:46.180
But Jeremy laid out the four essentials for what healthy church involvement looks like here.

00:46.160 --> 00:55.186
It's to gather on Sundays, engage the discipleship pathway, be involved in Christian community, and serve in some capacity.

00:55.746 --> 00:59.914
Now, last week we talked about the importance of gathering together for worship.

01:00.254 --> 01:06.265
We talked about how Sundays aren't just this formal tradition that we have, but we are coming here believing that God wants to meet with us.

01:06.926 --> 01:11.494
And that this is a unique way that we get to experience the presence of God as the people of God.

01:12.015 --> 01:17.906
And today we're going to continue on that conversation by talking about engaging the discipleship pathway.

01:18.722 --> 01:29.111
But before we get into the scripture and before we talk about what engaging the discipleship pathway means, I wanted to take a step back and explain why we need to talk about discipleship at all.

01:30.555 --> 01:34.386
To be a disciple means to be a learner or a student.

01:34.882 --> 01:37.687
And that doesn't just mean informal capacities.

01:38.408 --> 01:40.572
The truth is that we're all being discipled.

01:40.612 --> 01:46.984
We're all being formed by different beliefs, by different people, by different worldviews and more.

01:47.024 --> 01:52.434
And so whether you're here today and you're on a Christian or you're not, you behave a certain way.

01:52.770 --> 01:59.721
something is influencing you to behave a certain way, to speak a certain way, even to think a certain way.

02:00.082 --> 02:05.070
And it doesn't matter what environment you're in, you are being formed to believe certain things.

02:05.892 --> 02:12.282
Which I feel like a lot of us in LA don't like to admit that this is true because the West Coast land of free thinkers, right?

02:13.063 --> 02:19.634
But have you ever considered that the only reason you think that you're a free thinker is because the environment you're in is telling you you're a free thinker?

02:20.418 --> 02:25.888
Like we are formed by, if you grew up in rural Missouri, maybe some of you did, you probably would think differently.

02:27.490 --> 02:38.149
My brother and I, we grew up here in Southern California, but when he was a teenager, he moved over to Missouri and is, I mean, he's raising seven kids for now, probably more in the future.

02:39.251 --> 02:43.098
His kids love the rodeo, like, you know, there's like four year olds riding bowls and stuff.

02:44.380 --> 02:45.682
I've forgotten all their names.

02:46.274 --> 02:48.537
But that's kind of what his life is like.

02:48.577 --> 02:52.061
And over the, he's been there for 15, 20 years and I've been able to like observe and see.

02:52.482 --> 02:57.589
And at first I was honestly, I'm a little judgmental and I was like, man, this is such a bubble.

02:57.649 --> 03:03.056
Like, you know, I wonder if they like understand there's more than crops.

03:03.877 --> 03:12.067
And, but then the more I've like talked with my brother, I realized, shoot, I'm in a bubble.

03:12.808 --> 03:14.290
Like LA is a bubble.

03:14.690 --> 03:21.588
And like talking to my brother has made me realize it's not just the people out there, it's me and us here in this city.

03:24.035 --> 03:28.146
Now we are formed by our environments around us.

03:28.386 --> 03:33.235
Even, I mean, you think about the way you go to work in this city, the way you think about success or failure.

03:33.535 --> 03:39.065
This city wants you to take its convictions and its passions and to believe certain things.

03:39.506 --> 03:41.369
And to be clear, I'm not saying it's all bad.

03:41.429 --> 03:44.876
I'm not saying the way that you're being influenced is all necessarily bad things.

03:45.437 --> 03:48.522
But I think we need to honestly say, I am being formed.

03:48.823 --> 03:51.448
We are being formed by our environments.

03:52.549 --> 03:52.850
Now,

03:53.090 --> 03:59.157
We're all disciples of something or somebody, but to be a Christian means that you are a disciple of Jesus.

04:00.679 --> 04:10.451
Now, again, some of you might be here and you're not a Christian and you might be thinking, if Christians are supposed to be influenced by Christ, why do so many Christians not look like Jesus?

04:11.452 --> 04:12.333
Which is a good question.

04:12.393 --> 04:19.922
And some of you, maybe you are Christians and you're thinking about all the people you know that don't really look like Jesus.

04:22.050 --> 04:24.474
But the reality is we all have our own blind spots.

04:24.534 --> 04:30.342
And before we judge what other people are experiencing, we need to look internally and say, where am I at?

04:30.503 --> 04:31.825
And what is God doing with me?

04:31.865 --> 04:37.653
Not that we don't address the other things, but we first look inward so our posture is humble.

04:37.874 --> 04:48.850
And I believe today that as we talk about discipleship, I believe God wants to expose some of those things for us, not out of condemnation, but out of grace to grow us and to change us.

04:49.058 --> 04:59.874
It seems to me that a lot of the church is in a discipleship drought, that in some spaces, Christians are being taught what they should believe, but not how they should behave.

05:01.196 --> 05:07.065
And in other spaces, Christians are being taught how they should behave, but they're being taught to ignore what the Bible teaches.

05:09.569 --> 05:18.322
Being a disciple of Jesus, there's always gonna be a form of counter formation, which means recognizing the ways we're formed so we can go to Jesus and say, reform me.

05:19.266 --> 05:20.047
Change me.

05:20.087 --> 05:24.693
And this is a really important aspect of repentance.

05:25.574 --> 05:33.604
See, when we talk about repentance, oftentimes the thing that gets pointed out is that repentance means to change your actions, to do a 180, which is good and true.

05:34.305 --> 05:37.289
But the word repentance literally means to change your mind.

05:38.871 --> 05:40.813
Repentance doesn't start with changing your actions.

05:40.914 --> 05:42.936
It starts with changing your mind.

05:43.617 --> 05:47.602
If you think about this, you can change your actions and still have the same mindset.

05:47.906 --> 05:50.670
I can do something loving for you out of bitterness and resentment.

05:53.233 --> 06:00.824
You can do the right things for the wrong reasons, but repentance means changing your mind and letting the actions change from there.

06:02.025 --> 06:06.992
Now, my wife gets annoyed off and after a reminder of this, but I need to remind her that I'm colorblind.

06:07.793 --> 06:10.036
And every time there's like, well, whatever, I'm not going to go there.

06:10.196 --> 06:11.378
I'm colorblind.

06:11.522 --> 06:13.265
which doesn't mean I can't see color.

06:13.625 --> 06:16.510
It means that I get certain colors confused, okay?

06:16.910 --> 06:20.175
So blues and purples sometimes look similar to me, reds and greens.

06:20.195 --> 06:25.723
You can imagine Christmas time is difficult, but reds and greens sometimes look very similar to me.

06:25.764 --> 06:36.520
And I remember I realized this when in fourth grade, you know the tests that have all the color dots on it and you're trying to see numbers and I was like, I don't see everybody around me in my class was like, oh yeah, there's a six.

06:36.540 --> 06:38.563
And I was like, I see nothing in this.

06:39.204 --> 06:40.626
And so I realized I was color blind.

06:41.730 --> 06:44.333
Now, I've had people say, why don't you try those color blind glasses?

06:44.393 --> 06:48.617
Where it shows you what color looks like with, I guess, normal human beings, what it looks like.

06:50.499 --> 06:55.965
Now, imagine I get those glasses, I put them on, and I finally can see the contrast between blue and purple.

06:56.526 --> 07:04.574
And I see a beautiful green Douglas fir tree, and I see the red ornaments popping out, and I'm like, dang, this is beautiful.

07:04.614 --> 07:08.018
But then I take the glasses off, and I'm back to seeing things the way that I see them.

07:08.770 --> 07:12.233
Now, my reality is I can't see reds and greens very easily.

07:13.154 --> 07:20.001
But the only reason I believe that I see color incorrectly is because I've accepted that there is something true that I cannot see.

07:21.622 --> 07:25.686
That reality exists in a way that my eyes are telling me is different.

07:27.448 --> 07:34.174
Now, scripture claims that it offers us the correct and the true way to view the world.

07:34.815 --> 07:38.098
And if you are a Christian, you are choosing to surrender yourself.

07:39.330 --> 07:47.619
to what scripture says is true, even if it contradicts your own preconceived notions or what the world around you is saying.

07:48.961 --> 07:53.606
Scripture teaches that God created the heavens and the earth and that he sustains all things by the word of his power.

07:54.447 --> 07:58.632
Scripture teaches that God created the universe good, but human sin broke it.

07:59.673 --> 08:07.922
Scripture teaches that we are, by nature, sinful, that we are children of wrath who are self-centered and separated from God.

08:08.930 --> 08:12.273
But God loves this so much that He didn't leave us to die in our own sin.

08:13.014 --> 08:17.539
He sent His Son to the earth to live and die for us so that we could be saved.

08:18.279 --> 08:24.666
And Jesus, the Son of God rose from the dead and sent the Holy Spirit to dwell in us.

08:25.407 --> 08:32.754
And Scripture says, Jesus is coming back to judge the living and the dead and that those who trust in Him will be raised to life everlasting.

08:32.974 --> 08:34.196
That's what Scripture teaches.

08:34.436 --> 08:36.658
And if you're a Christian, you're saying, I believe that.

08:38.338 --> 08:45.067
The more you know Jesus, the more you learn from Jesus, the more you become like Jesus.

08:45.948 --> 08:53.078
And this church, this is God's ultimate goal for you is to become like Jesus.

08:54.200 --> 08:55.321
This is not my opinion.

08:55.381 --> 08:56.683
This is in Scripture.

08:57.484 --> 09:05.996
Scripture says this Romans 828, and we know that for all those who love God, all things work together for good for those who are called according to his purpose.

09:06.557 --> 09:07.378
Beautiful verse.

09:07.522 --> 09:07.843
Right?

09:08.243 --> 09:11.749
It completely reframes with the way we think about suffering, the way we think about pain.

09:12.230 --> 09:17.199
It reframes the way that we think about hope and what our hope is for the future.

09:17.239 --> 09:22.227
But have you ever looked at that verse and wondered, well, God's working all things together for good.

09:22.288 --> 09:23.750
What is the good?

09:25.253 --> 09:28.318
If he's working all for good, what is the good that he's working it toward?

09:29.180 --> 09:32.946
Well, Roman tells us the next verse, Romans 8, 29.

09:33.026 --> 09:38.393
For those whom he foreign you, he also predestined to be conformed to the image of his son.

09:39.555 --> 09:52.192
So the goal that God has for you, his chief goal for you as a follower of Jesus, which by the way is the greatest good for you, his chief goal is making you fully into the image of his son, Jesus.

09:53.914 --> 09:57.919
Following Jesus isn't just about saving you from your sin, it is, but it's about more than that.

09:58.400 --> 10:00.082
It's not just about everlasting life,

10:00.546 --> 10:03.430
It is about Jesus making you more and more like him.

10:03.771 --> 10:07.496
That's his goal, and that's why we need to talk about discipleship this morning at church.

10:09.379 --> 10:16.248
Now, one of the more common metaphors that Jesus uses to talk about discipleship is that of a flock of sheep and a shepherd.

10:16.549 --> 10:21.396
So we're gonna read from John 22, excuse me, John 10 this morning, verses 22 through 30.

10:21.436 --> 10:22.637
If you have your Bible, you can turn there.

10:23.138 --> 10:25.301
If not, you can follow along, it'll be on the screen behind me.

10:26.723 --> 10:28.626
So John 10, 22 through 30.

10:30.434 --> 10:34.398
At that time, the feast of dedication took place at Jerusalem.

10:35.520 --> 10:39.905
It was winter, and Jesus was walking in the temple in the colonnade of Solomon.

10:40.886 --> 10:46.152
So the Jews gathered around him and said to him, how long will you keep us in suspense?

10:46.172 --> 10:47.913
If you are the Christ, tell us plainly.

10:49.175 --> 10:52.178
Jesus answered them, I told you, and you do not believe.

10:53.119 --> 10:59.186
The works that I do in my father's name bear witness about me, but you do not believe because you are not part of my flock.

11:00.098 --> 11:03.263
My sheep hear my voice and I know them and they follow me.

11:03.283 --> 11:08.691
I give them eternal life and they will never perish and no one will snatch them out of my hand.

11:09.693 --> 11:15.121
My father who has given them to me is greater than all and no one is able to snatch them out of my father's hand.

11:15.141 --> 11:17.325
I and the father are one.

11:18.306 --> 11:19.068
This is the word of God.

11:19.108 --> 11:19.628
Pray with me.

11:21.071 --> 11:25.778
Lord, as we approach our word, we recognize that we need you to change the way that we see things.

11:26.338 --> 11:28.461
to help us see things the way that you see things.

11:28.822 --> 11:37.715
And Lord, I'm grateful that you have a vested interest in our discipleship that is not us trying to work hard, it is you forming the character of Christ in us.

11:38.235 --> 11:44.825
I pray Jesus that you would form us this morning, shift our eyes, help us to see things the way that you do and draw us to yourself.

11:45.366 --> 11:48.050
Lord, we come before you humbly as the people who are in need.

11:48.550 --> 11:50.053
Speak to us, we pray in your name, Jesus.

11:50.533 --> 11:50.994
Amen.

11:52.770 --> 11:58.661
So Jesus was in Jerusalem, it says during the Feast of Dedication, which in Hebrew is Hanukkah.

11:58.681 --> 12:06.535
This feast was established in Jerusalem in 164 BC when the Jews revolted against the Syrian king Antiochus Epiphanes.

12:07.336 --> 12:17.234
Antiochus was obsessed with Greek culture and he decided he wanted to eliminate Jewish culture and infuse all of his gods and all of his power into Palestine.

12:17.410 --> 12:21.296
And in the year 170, he attacked Jerusalem, 170 BC before Jesus.

12:21.596 --> 12:27.645
He attacked Jerusalem and is said to have killed 80,000 Jews and then taken another 80,000 as slaves.

12:28.667 --> 12:37.099
Antiochus made a capital offense in Jerusalem to own a copy of the law of Moses and he made it illegal to circumcise your children.

12:37.560 --> 12:42.407
And if you did that, he would crucify you and he would hang your children by your neck.

12:43.949 --> 12:46.994
Antiochus profaned the temple in Jerusalem.

12:47.714 --> 12:54.787
He turned the chambers into brothels and he dedicated the altar to Zeus by sacrificing swine on it.

12:56.309 --> 13:00.557
But a man named Judas Maccabeus and his brother raised up a group to fight back.

13:00.577 --> 13:02.560
And they finally defeated Antiochus in 164.

13:02.841 --> 13:03.843
They cleansed the temple.

13:04.123 --> 13:07.028
They purified the altar so they could worship Yahweh again.

13:07.048 --> 13:09.292
And that's why it's called the Feast of Dedication.

13:09.312 --> 13:10.354
They took back

13:10.434 --> 13:13.922
the altar and rededicated it to God.

13:14.222 --> 13:20.336
And now you fast forward 200 years about, to where Jesus comes, into Jerusalem during this feast.

13:21.779 --> 13:26.770
And in Jesus's day, Jerusalem wasn't occupied by Syria, they were occupied by Rome.

13:27.298 --> 13:34.948
And the Jewish people were waiting for another savior, like Judas Maccabeus, who could rise up and fight off Rome and free Israel.

13:35.449 --> 13:49.488
And the concept that the Jews had was that of a Messiah, or in Greek Christ, a Messiah who would come up and defeat their enemies and free them from oppression and usher them into a golden era of prosperity once again.

13:49.549 --> 13:53.554
Well, many people were wondering, is Jesus this Messiah?

13:54.946 --> 13:57.390
I mean, he was making a number of claims that were huge.

13:57.871 --> 14:01.256
And he was performing these signs and miracles and everyone's thinking, shoot, this might be it.

14:02.078 --> 14:05.643
This guy might be the guy that saves us from oppression.

14:05.824 --> 14:09.149
But then Jesus wasn't doing the things that they wanted him to do or thought he should do.

14:09.810 --> 14:12.114
The things Jesus was doing were unexpected.

14:12.642 --> 14:13.483
and confusing.

14:13.523 --> 14:25.835
And so we read in John 10 that the Jews come to Jesus during the Feast of Dedication where they're celebrating the Savior from 200 years before, hoping for a Savior to come again, they go to Jesus and they say, how long will you keep us in suspense?

14:26.435 --> 14:28.397
If you are the Christ, tell us plainly.

14:28.437 --> 14:37.386
Now this might seem like an earnest question, but another way you can translate this first statement is, how long are you gonna annoy us?

14:39.488 --> 14:41.330
And so they're going to Jesus and

14:41.442 --> 14:43.866
In reality, they already know who Jesus is claiming to be.

14:43.926 --> 14:45.328
They already know this.

14:45.368 --> 15:00.213
I mean, you can read this before in the book of John, but even right after this story in John 33, 1033, it says the Jews answered Jesus, it's not for a good work that we're going to stone you, but for blasphemy because you, being a man, make yourself God.

15:01.335 --> 15:05.642
Okay, so the crowd knew who Jesus claimed to be and they wanted to kill him.

15:05.722 --> 15:08.306
So this question wasn't earnest, it was a trap.

15:08.834 --> 15:12.318
It was, can we get you to say something that will justify us stoning you right now?

15:14.100 --> 15:21.308
Now, Jesus says to them in verse 25, I told you and you do not believe the works that I deal with my father's name bear witness about me.

15:22.088 --> 15:24.611
And so the problem is not that Jesus isn't being clear.

15:24.651 --> 15:27.695
The problem is that the people are refusing to believe it.

15:29.757 --> 15:31.379
Jesus said, it's not even just my words.

15:31.419 --> 15:32.700
It's the works that I'm doing.

15:33.121 --> 15:34.482
You're seeing me do stuff.

15:34.946 --> 15:36.448
in the Father's name.

15:36.649 --> 15:38.571
And in verse 30, he even goes further.

15:38.671 --> 15:42.097
In verse 30, he says, I and the Father are one.

15:44.260 --> 15:49.467
What Jesus is doing is he's claiming that when you see Jesus' work, you are seeing God work.

15:49.487 --> 15:52.452
And when you see God work, you are seeing Jesus' work.

15:53.153 --> 15:55.476
The Father and Jesus have the same goal.

15:55.777 --> 16:00.704
And either way, when they are working, they are accomplishing their unified goal.

16:01.024 --> 16:04.850
And notice, Jesus is not saying that he and the Father are the same person.

16:04.930 --> 16:05.190
Right?

16:05.310 --> 16:07.994
I mean, if that was the case, they could have just said he's a lunatic.

16:08.655 --> 16:10.437
And like, there's would have been a lot easier for them.

16:11.018 --> 16:11.719
It's he's crazy.

16:11.739 --> 16:12.540
He doesn't know what he's saying.

16:12.900 --> 16:17.286
They understand what Jesus is doing is saying, I am equal to God.

16:17.666 --> 16:19.609
What you see God doing is what I am doing.

16:19.909 --> 16:21.631
I and the Father are one.

16:23.053 --> 16:25.636
And this is where Jesus gets into this metaphor of sheep.

16:26.217 --> 16:31.544
In verse 25, he says, you do not believe because you are not my sheep.

16:32.786 --> 16:33.106
Now,

16:33.186 --> 16:37.972
Think about how offensive this is, because Jesus is talking to God's flock.

16:39.193 --> 16:47.704
He's talking to the people of Israel, the children of Abraham, who God said, you are my chosen people to be a light to the nations.

16:48.044 --> 16:51.008
And Jesus says, yeah, the reason you don't believe me is because you're not.

16:52.310 --> 16:54.252
You're not actually part of God's flock.

16:57.196 --> 17:02.162
Being associated with God's people does not make you God's people.

17:03.778 --> 17:09.625
You can be a really good person who looks like a model Christian, but if you miss Jesus, you miss everything.

17:11.868 --> 17:16.373
Churches, we talk about the essentials and what church involvement looks like the next few weeks.

17:16.774 --> 17:21.139
Do not mistake being involved in church rhythms for actually being a part of God's family.

17:22.181 --> 17:26.226
Do not focus on your actions with not looking at your own heart.

17:26.666 --> 17:33.074
Jesus says if you do that, you're like cleaning the cup on the outside and forgetting that you kind of need to clean the inside too.

17:34.882 --> 17:37.926
Healthy church involvement is really important, but that's not what saves you.

17:38.046 --> 17:40.129
That's what you do if you are saved.

17:42.613 --> 17:49.963
God is not interested in your performance or your commitment to church tradition if it doesn't come with your heart.

17:51.104 --> 17:52.907
Obedience without love means nothing.

17:53.407 --> 17:54.168
God wants you.

17:56.672 --> 17:59.616
So Jesus, he goes on to talk about the sheep.

18:01.218 --> 18:04.082
And he says that there are three attributes of his sheep.

18:04.290 --> 18:07.334
three things that show who his sheep are.

18:08.015 --> 18:10.559
In verse 27, he says, my sheep hear my voice.

18:11.500 --> 18:13.543
I know them, they follow me.

18:15.546 --> 18:18.229
And you'll notice right off the bat that these are not commands.

18:19.151 --> 18:21.894
Jesus is not telling you what to do if you wanna be a sheep.

18:22.235 --> 18:24.518
He's giving you a description of what sheep do.

18:26.100 --> 18:29.645
Jesus is not telling the Jews, hey, if you wanna be a part of God's family, do these things.

18:29.906 --> 18:33.170
He's saying, this is what God's family does.

18:33.474 --> 18:37.642
Jesus' goal here is not to explain how to become sheep, it's to explain what the sheep do.

18:37.982 --> 18:40.928
And the first thing he says is that the sheep hear his voice.

18:42.290 --> 18:50.205
Now, it's been said that shepherds often knew all of their sheep by name and the sheep actually could tell their shepherds' voice from others.

18:50.726 --> 18:57.138
And so a lot of ancient shepherds, they wouldn't get nervous if their flocks grazed with other flocks because they knew they could just call out.

18:57.250 --> 18:58.772
and gather their sheep to themselves.

18:58.832 --> 19:04.481
I even read one story, I think this was more modern day, but a shepherd played his flute all the time for the sheep.

19:05.001 --> 19:12.853
And when his sheep were with another three or four flocks, he just played his flute and his sheep lifted their heads and came over to him.

19:14.415 --> 19:20.464
So to hear the voice of Jesus saying, my sheep hear my voice, he's not saying that you audibly notice somebody talking.

19:21.545 --> 19:24.690
I love how theologian Samuel Naguis says this, he says,

19:24.898 --> 19:30.506
Listening here includes both hearing with one's ears and responding in obedience from one's heart.

19:31.407 --> 19:33.870
And so Jesus isn't saying that sheep just hear his voice.

19:34.291 --> 19:38.517
He's saying his sheep hear his voice and respond in obedience.

19:38.537 --> 19:42.842
And as a side note, this is one of the reasons it's so vital to be in Scripture often.

19:43.443 --> 19:48.330
Scripture isn't like the thing you do to be a good Christian, but if you want to be familiar with God's voice, read Scripture.

19:49.031 --> 19:50.853
Scripture is the authoritative word of God.

19:50.873 --> 19:54.258
If you want to know God's voice in all of your life, read Scripture a lot.

19:54.402 --> 19:57.509
And then you'll get familiar and you'll know his voice in the rest of life.

19:58.150 --> 20:00.195
So Jesus says, my sheep, they hear my voice.

20:00.235 --> 20:02.179
They know my voice and they respond.

20:03.522 --> 20:08.874
The second attribute of sheep, Jesus says that he knows his sheep.

20:09.255 --> 20:10.197
He knows his sheep.

20:11.821 --> 20:14.066
Now, if Jesus is God, then technically he knows everybody.

20:14.338 --> 20:22.330
So clearly, Jesus is not talking about just knowing somebody, that all the sheep, he's saying a particular type of knowing here.

20:22.831 --> 20:33.087
The fifth century theologian from Egypt, Cyril of Alexandria, he said, no one is entirely unknown by God, but to be known in this way is to become part of his family.

20:34.229 --> 20:38.476
So Jesus doesn't just know who his sheep are, he knows them personally.

20:39.117 --> 20:42.642
There is a relationship, not just an awareness of a person,

20:43.554 --> 20:47.279
Now, Jesus can know you because he's God and he knows all things.

20:48.060 --> 20:51.043
But can you say that Jesus knows you because you have a relationship with him?

20:52.886 --> 20:56.110
Are you able to say that Jesus knows you because you are letting him know you?

20:58.833 --> 21:00.795
God's desire is for relationship.

21:01.937 --> 21:05.862
The relationship with God is what we lost in the Garden of Eden when sin entered the world.

21:06.483 --> 21:08.485
We became separated from God.

21:09.166 --> 21:12.530
And it's what Jesus restored when he died on the cross for our sins.

21:13.346 --> 21:17.551
And so following Jesus isn't primarily about us doing good things for God.

21:17.631 --> 21:22.057
It's about being with Jesus and cultivating our relationship with Jesus.

21:22.237 --> 21:28.725
There's this really beautiful passage in Mark, Mark chapter three, where it talks about Jesus calling the 12 apostles to himself.

21:29.366 --> 21:38.016
And it says that Jesus called the 12 first so that they might be with him, then that he might send them out to have authority over the demons and preach the gospel.

21:38.998 --> 21:42.642
Jesus said, first, I'm calling you to be with me.

21:43.778 --> 21:48.424
Jesus wants relationship for you to know him and to be known by him.

21:48.684 --> 21:52.789
And so being a disciple doesn't mean doing things for Jesus, it means knowing Jesus.

21:54.391 --> 21:57.114
So Jesus says, he knows his sheep, he knows us.

21:57.475 --> 22:00.138
And earlier in John, it says that the sheep know Jesus.

22:02.121 --> 22:06.546
The third attribute of his sheep, Jesus says, his sheep follow him.

22:08.226 --> 22:16.075
Now, for a lot of people who grow up in religious environments, it can be easy to miss the fact that Jesus doesn't just want a part of you, he wants all of you.

22:16.115 --> 22:21.341
As followers of Jesus, we're learning to follow Jesus in all of life.

22:23.243 --> 22:27.147
We don't leave parts of ourselves, we give our whole selves to Jesus.

22:29.150 --> 22:36.498
Some of you are good at following Jesus in your actions, but you just can't seem to accept the things that Jesus taught.

22:38.818 --> 22:44.907
You've ordered your life in a way that shows love and compassion, but you ignore the teachings of Jesus when they're hard or challenge you.

22:46.649 --> 22:50.574
You don't want to ruffle feathers, you'd rather just imitate Jesus' actions and not repeat his words.

22:52.237 --> 22:54.820
But you can't follow Jesus if you don't believe what Jesus said.

22:57.224 --> 23:01.650
Some of you are good at believing what Jesus said, but you don't sound like Jesus.

23:03.330 --> 23:09.439
You've bought into the lie that saying the truth is inherently loving even if it's said without love, which is not in the Bible.

23:11.181 --> 23:15.067
Speaking the truth without love is worse than saying nothing at all.

23:15.968 --> 23:22.317
And you'd be wise to remember that the people that Jesus had the harshest words for were the religious people who knew the right things to say.

23:22.357 --> 23:31.570
Following Jesus doesn't just believe in correct doctrine, it means imitating Jesus in your words and in your tone and in your deeds.

23:33.058 --> 23:35.702
Some of you are actually pretty good at sounding like Jesus.

23:36.623 --> 23:42.071
You know the right words to say and you look really spiritual, but secretly you ignore what Jesus tells you to do.

23:43.953 --> 23:45.636
You don't care to honor him with your body.

23:46.637 --> 23:49.301
You ignore the fact that God calls us to live holy because he is holy.

23:50.783 --> 23:54.808
But we have to accept the ethics of Jesus, even when it's contrary to the world around us.

23:55.209 --> 23:58.834
Following Jesus means living in a way that reflects him.

24:01.538 --> 24:04.061
Some of you today are holding back pieces of your life.

24:05.583 --> 24:10.750
Maybe you don't want to change and you're living your life for yourself and you haven't realized the emptiness of that yet.

24:12.572 --> 24:13.693
Maybe you're afraid of changing.

24:13.734 --> 24:18.299
I mean, it can be scary to surrender, to give up and surrender to something bigger than yourself.

24:19.661 --> 24:24.908
But remember, God's chief good for you is to make you more like Jesus.

24:25.609 --> 24:27.992
And God isn't trying to change you because he's unhappy with you.

24:28.332 --> 24:29.874
He's trying to change you because he loves you.

24:31.522 --> 24:40.196
I know that for many of you, maybe even the Spirit's convicting you of certain things right now, but you need to understand if you feel that conviction, you need to recognize where it's coming from.

24:41.057 --> 24:43.822
It's coming from a loving Father who is patient with you.

24:44.703 --> 24:49.511
A loving Father who is like a surgeon that wounds to heal.

24:51.574 --> 24:56.442
God isn't revealing sin or areas of immaturity in your life to shame you.

24:56.642 --> 24:58.866
He's revealing it to walk with you.

24:58.978 --> 25:02.804
and to change you and to grow you as you surrender yourself to Him.

25:03.144 --> 25:06.830
Remember, God has a vested interest in your becoming more like Jesus.

25:07.531 --> 25:08.973
This process is a partnership.

25:09.614 --> 25:13.180
God is not saying, do the right things become like Jesus and I'll meet you at the finish line.

25:13.941 --> 25:15.183
That's not what's happening here.

25:15.804 --> 25:20.330
Jesus promises to be with us each step of the way as we work toward becoming like Jesus.

25:21.152 --> 25:27.922
This is why Paul the Apostle in Philippians two, verses 12 through 13, he says, work out your own salvation with fear and trembling.

25:28.258 --> 25:33.804
For it is God who works in you, both to will and to work for his good pleasure.

25:34.245 --> 25:36.087
Church, God is committed to your growth.

25:37.288 --> 25:38.850
Are you committed to your growth with him?

25:41.913 --> 25:46.638
I hope it's a little more clear even now why we need to talk about discipleship and why this is so important.

25:46.818 --> 25:49.581
And I hope it's a little more clear what it means to be a disciple of Jesus.

25:49.942 --> 25:57.490
But now I want to circle back to the beginning of this and talk about what we're talking about today, engaging the discipleship pathway.

25:57.794 --> 26:00.781
Right, that's the focus for today, engaging the discipleship pathway.

26:01.583 --> 26:05.712
On Vision Sunday, we put out a survey, and about 500 people, I believe, filled that out.

26:06.193 --> 26:10.884
And one of the questions on it was, have you completed reality LA's discipleship pathway online?

26:11.164 --> 26:12.227
And here are the results.

26:12.247 --> 26:12.989
They should be behind me.

26:13.249 --> 26:13.470
Okay.

26:13.490 --> 26:17.138
4% of you said you don't know what it is.

26:17.378 --> 26:18.940
Which is, I mean, that's not very many people.

26:19.100 --> 26:23.445
The only concerning thing about that is Jeremy just told you what it is before he told you to follow the survey.

26:25.147 --> 26:26.488
But it will just pretend that that's not real.

26:26.508 --> 26:29.171
4% of it, you said you don't know what it is.

26:29.191 --> 26:31.073
7% of you said you started it, didn't complain it.

26:31.093 --> 26:32.895
19% of you said you completed it.

26:33.136 --> 26:35.038
And 70% of you said you have not done it.

26:35.779 --> 26:39.182
Now, based on these survey results, I think there are three questions that we need to answer.

26:39.283 --> 26:43.908
If we're gonna prioritize engaging the discipleship pathway this year, three questions that we need to answer.

26:45.069 --> 26:45.970
First question.

26:46.306 --> 26:47.768
What is the discipleship pathway?

26:49.330 --> 26:50.371
Honestly, it's a good question.

26:51.372 --> 26:57.360
The discipleship pathway is a tool that we created to help us understand what it looks like to follow Jesus in all of life.

26:58.221 --> 27:03.247
The discipleship pathway covers 12 key dynamics that show what a life renewed by Jesus looks like.

27:03.988 --> 27:15.442
And while these 12 dynamics are not the whole of Christian life, we believe that somebody who follows Jesus as a way of life in all of life, that they will consistently engage and grow in these areas over time.

27:16.482 --> 27:20.468
The discipleship pathway is a great tool for new believers and seasoned believers.

27:20.508 --> 27:23.633
It's not a class that you graduate from or a box you check off.

27:23.973 --> 27:27.518
It's a tool to use to grow in following Jesus.

27:28.219 --> 27:32.946
It's also a tool that you can use as you show other people how to follow Jesus.

27:33.647 --> 27:40.978
One of our convictions as a church and as more broadly as Christians is that the disciples of Jesus make disciples of Jesus.

27:42.018 --> 27:47.603
I mean, that's honestly the only reason we're here right now is because the 12 apostles heard Jesus say, go and make disciples.

27:47.623 --> 27:49.185
And they said, okay, and they did it.

27:49.585 --> 27:51.267
And then the disciples, they made did it.

27:51.547 --> 27:55.291
And then they kept on going until 2000 years later, we're sitting here, right?

27:55.751 --> 28:01.237
And so we take that up seriously, that Jesus has called us to make disciples of Jesus.

28:02.158 --> 28:07.463
We take that upon ourselves, to show people the beauty of the gospel and what it looks like to follow him.

28:08.083 --> 28:10.706
And in part, this is because we're not just concerned with ourselves.

28:11.842 --> 28:13.584
We want to tell other people about Jesus.

28:13.644 --> 28:16.127
We want to show other people why this isn't just some worldview.

28:16.147 --> 28:18.349
We believe this is how the world really is.

28:20.011 --> 28:28.441
The discipleship pathway is a great tool that you can help walk other people through what life looks like following Jesus, whether they met him yesterday or 30 years ago.

28:28.461 --> 28:40.114
Now, we obviously don't have the time or the attention span for that matter to dive deeply into all 12 of these right now, but I'm just going to list them out and make a comment, probably just one comment on each word willing.

28:40.354 --> 28:43.538
Okay, the first one, dynamic number one is the story of Scripture.

28:44.800 --> 28:50.608
And this dynamic reminds us that Scripture shows us the world as it really is, and we seek to live by that story.

28:51.509 --> 28:53.111
Dynamic number two, knowing God.

28:53.792 --> 29:00.061
That God's primary desire is for us to know Him, not just to do things for Him, but to know Him deeply.

29:00.341 --> 29:01.142
And how do we do that?

29:01.162 --> 29:01.943
What does that look like?

29:02.004 --> 29:03.365
That's what this dynamic explores.

29:04.347 --> 29:05.849
Dynamic three, identity in Christ.

29:06.470 --> 29:09.714
Faith in Jesus makes us new creations, which means

29:09.858 --> 29:13.302
When you follow Jesus, you're becoming who you already are in Him.

29:13.362 --> 29:17.987
And you need to know who you are before you start trying to be that person yourself.

29:19.068 --> 29:25.955
Dynamic four, formative practices, we cultivate spiritual practices that shape us into Christ-like character.

29:26.356 --> 29:29.379
It's kind of part of what Nathan was talking about earlier with the church calendar, right?

29:29.659 --> 29:34.124
We set up practices to form us into Christ-like character.

29:34.745 --> 29:35.666
Dynamic five,

29:35.746 --> 29:40.150
Healthy relationships, we're committed to loving each other because we are committed to loving Jesus together.

29:40.190 --> 29:43.594
Dynamic six, healing from wounds.

29:43.914 --> 29:48.178
We are wounded in relationships and can experience healing in relationships with God and with each other.

29:48.519 --> 29:53.784
And this is an important one because we've all got wounds and we don't always realize when those wounds are projecting on other people.

29:54.244 --> 29:57.427
So knowing yourself and knowing how you're broken is going to help you follow Jesus.

29:58.428 --> 30:04.274
Dynamic seven, known in community, we're a new family made up of people from different backgrounds who learned to share life together.

30:05.058 --> 30:06.562
Dynamic 8 belong to a church.

30:07.123 --> 30:10.150
As a new family, we are committed to the well-being of one another.

30:11.092 --> 30:16.004
Dynamic 9 witness to Christ, we share the good news of Jesus with other people, and we make disciples.

30:16.826 --> 30:18.129
Dynamic 10, do justice.

30:18.671 --> 30:23.442
We recognize the dignity of all human beings, and we seek equity and order for human flourishing.

30:24.290 --> 30:26.113
Dynamic 11, we work with God.

30:26.153 --> 30:34.028
We follow Jesus in the unique callings that we all have in our workspaces, whether it's working for money or not for money.

30:34.068 --> 30:36.993
We are doing things with Jesus in our work.

30:37.514 --> 30:44.146
And Dynamic 12, make culture that as we live as a new family, it brings change and transformation to the world around us.

30:44.322 --> 30:47.427
So those are the 12 dynamics that we say, the 12 dynamics of renewal.

30:47.887 --> 30:50.511
And we made some videos for these dynamics.

30:50.531 --> 30:54.497
We made some discussion questions, reflection questions for you to go through in small groups.

30:54.798 --> 30:56.100
All that is available online.

30:56.320 --> 30:58.082
So that's what the discipleship pathway is.

30:58.303 --> 31:01.387
If you all took the survey today, you would all say, I at least know what it is, right?

31:02.249 --> 31:02.529
Okay.

31:03.671 --> 31:07.216
I almost like actually asked you to tell me, but that might be a little chaotic.

31:08.218 --> 31:09.600
Okay, so that's what the discipleship pathway is.

31:09.640 --> 31:13.906
Second question, why is the discipleship pathway important?

31:14.146 --> 31:18.111
I hope that it kind of already answered that with the rest of this sermon.

31:18.752 --> 31:20.434
But let me give you a couple of other reasons here.

31:20.474 --> 31:23.057
First, these dynamics just come from scripture.

31:23.397 --> 31:26.601
So it's not like somebody made these up and was like, these will be cool to focus on.

31:27.042 --> 31:30.145
Yeah, I hope you see that we care about these, because the Bible cares about these things.

31:30.806 --> 31:39.036
But also, uniting around a shared discipleship pathway like this, it gives us a common understanding of discipleship as a church.

31:39.817 --> 31:43.922
It gives us a shared experience around what it looks like to follow Jesus.

31:44.194 --> 31:45.377
And it gives us language.

31:46.219 --> 31:49.987
So we can be united in how we talk about this together as a church.

31:50.248 --> 31:54.557
And so one of the reasons this is so important is because it unites us as a church.

31:54.638 --> 31:59.509
I mean, there's so many great churches in the city, but when we're coming together as a church, we're saying, this is who we are.

31:59.549 --> 32:01.874
This is what God's called us to do.

32:02.210 --> 32:05.635
And the discipleship pathway gives us a common framework for that.

32:05.916 --> 32:10.182
And to be extra clear on this, I'm not saying that you have to do this to be a disciple of Jesus.

32:10.743 --> 32:16.312
I'm saying if you're a part of reality, LA, this is the way that we are moving forward in discipleship as a church.

32:17.133 --> 32:18.876
So that's why the discipleship pathway is important.

32:18.916 --> 32:23.663
The third question, what does it mean to engage the discipleship pathway?

32:24.624 --> 32:26.327
What does it mean to engage the discipleship pathway?

32:26.547 --> 32:27.669
Well, on the one hand, you're doing it right now.

32:27.809 --> 32:28.370
So good job.

32:29.026 --> 32:32.290
You are engaging with the discipleship pathway because you are listening to me talk about it.

32:32.491 --> 32:34.514
And hopefully you're working through it internally for yourself.

32:35.675 --> 32:37.277
But I want to let you in on another secret.

32:38.199 --> 32:42.925
If you're a part of reality LA, you've already been engaging with the discipleship pathway, whether you realize it or not.

32:44.527 --> 32:46.650
Every Sunday we say our vision and mission statement, right?

32:46.690 --> 32:54.661
We are seeking the renewal of the city of Los Angeles through the good news of Jesus by making disciples who love, follow Jesus, love one another and serve Los Angeles.

32:55.242 --> 32:58.066
And here's the thing, the 12 dynamics of renewal

32:58.466 --> 33:00.409
are all embedded into the mission statement.

33:01.571 --> 33:05.136
And so we follow Jesus by accepting the story of Scripture.

33:07.099 --> 33:12.668
We follow Jesus by knowing God and understanding our identity in Christ and developing formative practices.

33:13.549 --> 33:19.218
We love one another by building healthy relationships, healing from wounds, being known in community and belonging to a church.

33:19.618 --> 33:24.985
We serve Los Angeles by witnessing to Christ doing justice, working with God and making culture.

33:25.245 --> 33:29.471
And so the 12 dynamics are deeply embedded in who we are as a church already.

33:30.372 --> 33:34.297
Secondly, our staff is organized according to our vision and mission.

33:34.858 --> 33:43.730
And so even if you think about this, if you're a part of a community group, or if you've talked to anybody on the community group team, you are engaging in the dynamic of being known in community.

33:45.090 --> 33:48.576
So most of what we do as a church is all embedded in this.

33:49.077 --> 33:53.505
Every Sunday, we have a scripture reading, which I know we're learning to, you know, participate in, right?

33:53.866 --> 33:54.587
By getting here on time.

33:55.168 --> 33:58.615
And the scripture reading for years followed the discipleship pathway.

33:59.035 --> 34:02.642
For years, it would be aligned with the different dynamics every single month.

34:03.970 --> 34:11.802
Lastly, as you guys walked in today, you may have seen there's a sign out there that talks about 2026 and all the things that we're doing this year as a church, so the things we plan to do.

34:12.383 --> 34:18.412
And on that board, you can see how all those things are connected to different dynamics of renewal.

34:19.253 --> 34:22.077
So there you go, you're all engaging with this more than you realized it.

34:22.137 --> 34:24.401
I just want to make the invisible visible so you understand.

34:24.441 --> 34:27.986
This is how we have organized as a church.

34:28.226 --> 34:34.873
So for 2026, what we are saying is we want you to engage with it more deeply and intentionally if you have not already.

34:35.774 --> 34:38.857
I know that many of you have gone through the online tools with small groups.

34:39.738 --> 34:41.900
Some of you have gone through discipleship cohorts, which is great.

34:42.440 --> 34:46.184
But I want to give you four practical ways you can engage with the discipleship pathway this year.

34:46.244 --> 34:48.767
And I want you just to choose one of them.

34:48.947 --> 34:50.629
You can choose multiple ones, but at least choose one.

34:51.730 --> 34:55.794
The first way you can engage in the discipleship pathway this year is by joining a discipleship cohort.

34:56.386 --> 34:58.329
Discipleship cohorts are a 10-week process.

34:58.910 --> 35:07.463
We're meeting after church immediately from 12 to 130, where we take small groups of people through the 12 dynamics of renewal in the context of small group discipleship.

35:08.064 --> 35:09.887
We're doing these cohorts three times this year.

35:09.907 --> 35:14.594
The first round starts today, actually, and there's about 100 people that are going through that today.

35:14.614 --> 35:16.957
There's no more space for that if you didn't sign up.

35:17.518 --> 35:21.885
But the next one will be starting mid-April after Easter.

35:22.266 --> 35:25.170
We will have ASL interpretation for that round.

35:25.250 --> 35:28.680
And then in the fall, we'll do a third round where we will also have childcare.

35:29.361 --> 35:35.097
So we hope that as many of you as possible, we'll go through the discipleship cohorts this year to engage with it.

35:35.438 --> 35:41.074
But secondly, if you can't do that, we would encourage you to utilize the online tool with other people that you know.

35:41.218 --> 35:46.587
Grab some people, I talked to a woman today, this morning, who's gonna ask a few people in her community group to go through it Saturday mornings.

35:47.127 --> 35:53.157
Do that, ask other people, hey, would you like to engage in these dynamics with me over, and you could do it in 10 weeks, in 10 months?

35:53.758 --> 35:56.062
There's no time stamp, you could do it however you see fit.

35:56.683 --> 35:58.646
But go through the content with some other people.

35:59.347 --> 36:04.054
Go through the content with a small group of people that you can grow close to and talk together about following Jesus.

36:05.236 --> 36:08.882
Third, you can go out to the courtyard and there's a table out there

36:09.378 --> 36:10.680
which I should have said this earlier.

36:10.740 --> 36:12.943
At the table, you can sign up for the cohorts for later this year.

36:13.424 --> 36:16.167
There's a QR code for that, but there's also little bookmarks.

36:16.668 --> 36:21.835
And if you just have a crazy year coming up and you're like, I don't know how I could commit to doing more, just grab a bookmark.

36:22.396 --> 36:25.140
The bookmark that has the 12 dynamics on it, put it in your Bible.

36:26.001 --> 36:29.105
Put it in a book that you're reading and just spend time this year reflecting on it.

36:29.366 --> 36:31.188
We as a church are engaging with it this year.

36:31.469 --> 36:32.370
You do that as well.

36:32.674 --> 36:35.921
engage with the discipleship pathway, even if it's just reflecting on the 12 dynamics.

36:36.622 --> 36:42.534
And lastly, if all of those things, number four, if all those things just feel like too much, just choose one of the four things or 12 things.

36:42.955 --> 36:46.121
Just choose one of the 12 and ask God, how do you wanna work this in me this year?

36:46.943 --> 36:52.274
How do you wanna shape me and form me and draw you to yourself and make me more like Jesus in this way?

36:53.122 --> 37:00.213
So in 2026, we wanna engage with a discipleship pathway and we want everybody to engage with it in some meaningful way.

37:00.553 --> 37:06.623
If you've already gone through it before, consider taking other people through it and showing people what it looks like to follow Jesus in that way.

37:08.165 --> 37:12.572
Now, I wanna close our time this morning by going back to the book of John for a moment.

37:13.794 --> 37:19.623
Because remember, Jesus describes the sheep, but he doesn't explain how to become a sheep in this passage.

37:19.643 --> 37:21.586
Earlier in John, he does this.

37:22.754 --> 37:29.524
In John 629, Jesus said, this is the work of God that you believe in Him who He has sent.

37:30.446 --> 37:37.696
And so if you're here today and you're not a Christian, the point isn't do these 12 things and then you're a Christian.

37:38.778 --> 37:41.001
The work of God is to believe in Jesus.

37:42.063 --> 37:49.033
The invitation for you is to trust in Jesus, to repent of your sin and say, I see things the way that God sees them.

37:51.036 --> 37:52.178
What God wants is

37:52.258 --> 37:54.682
to once your heart, he wants to forgive you.

37:55.002 --> 37:56.385
You don't have 10 steps to go through.

37:56.625 --> 37:57.647
You don't need to pay a fee.

37:57.707 --> 37:59.349
Jesus says, come to me.

38:00.731 --> 38:02.254
If you have faith, come to me.

38:03.976 --> 38:05.859
Now, in its own way, this is challenging.

38:05.880 --> 38:10.186
If you're not a Christian, it takes humility, acknowledging that you need a savior.

38:10.246 --> 38:13.231
It takes surrender, trusting Jesus with your life.

38:13.592 --> 38:17.618
And it takes faith to believe that Jesus is who he said he is.

38:17.698 --> 38:27.253
And so today, if you trust in Jesus, scripture says you become a new creature that you are given a new identity and that you are a child of God.

38:27.934 --> 38:37.108
And scripture says that God gives you his Holy Spirit to dwell in you and to walk with you and to change you and transform you into the image of Jesus.

38:37.749 --> 38:39.432
That's what it looks like to become a sheep.

38:39.912 --> 38:42.076
And then Jesus says, this is what the sheep do.

38:42.376 --> 38:46.162
They hear my voice, I know them, and they follow me.

38:47.202 --> 38:50.805
Now John 10, 28 through 29, Jesus closes with these words.

38:50.845 --> 38:59.033
He says, I give them my sheep eternal life and they will never perish and no one will snatch them out of my hand.

38:59.994 --> 39:06.120
My father who has given them to me is greater than all and no one is able to snatch them out of the father's hand.

39:07.941 --> 39:15.569
Jesus is saying that in him is eternal life and obviously that part of that is life everlasting, right?

39:15.589 --> 39:17.170
He says you will never perish

39:17.314 --> 39:18.856
But eternal life is more than that.

39:19.517 --> 39:22.362
Eternal life is where God's creation flourishes.

39:23.263 --> 39:28.171
Where God's creation functions the way it was meant to, where we are whole and complete.

39:29.673 --> 39:33.079
Eternal life is life everlasting as it should be.

39:33.119 --> 39:37.746
Like life everlasting the way things are does not sound good to me.

39:38.274 --> 39:41.960
But Jesus is saying, I give you eternal life, life in me.

39:42.440 --> 39:45.004
Life the way it was meant to be, no brokenness.

39:45.205 --> 39:48.610
You don't have any more wounds to heal from because they've been healed.

39:49.592 --> 39:51.074
That is what Jesus is saying.

39:51.294 --> 39:56.202
And what's so beautiful about the way he closes this is he says, nobody can take this from you.

39:57.764 --> 40:02.732
You're in the Father's hand and you think somebody can take you from God Almighty's hand?

40:02.752 --> 40:06.578
No, they can't.

40:06.658 --> 40:07.519
You are safe.

40:07.619 --> 40:10.664
You are secure in Christ Jesus.

40:12.346 --> 40:16.191
Because God is committed to you, you are secure in Christ.

40:16.592 --> 40:21.919
So following Jesus, engaging with the discipleship pathway this year, we are being with Jesus.

40:21.959 --> 40:24.823
We are learning from Jesus and we are becoming like Jesus.

40:24.863 --> 40:25.945
That's God's goal for us.

40:26.265 --> 40:27.667
And that's what we want to walk into this year.

40:27.727 --> 40:28.208
Amen, church.

40:29.029 --> 40:29.670
Amen, pray with me.

40:31.432 --> 40:32.754
Lord, we recognize that

40:34.466 --> 40:37.831
We need you to shape us and form us into Christ's character.

40:37.871 --> 40:46.443
And we understand that that's gonna happen as we come to you, Jesus, and rely on you and what you've done for us on the cross.

40:47.344 --> 40:55.835
Where I pray even this morning, I do pray for conviction if there are ways, immaturity or failures that you wanna expose in us and draw us closer to you with.

40:56.416 --> 40:59.180
Lord, would you do that gently and kindly in our hearts?

41:00.342 --> 41:03.506
Lord, I also just pray that you would help us to see you clearly

41:04.130 --> 41:08.995
that you are a good father, a good shepherd who walks his sheep to green pastures.

41:11.678 --> 41:16.424
Lord, any words of condemnation or shame that we're experiencing is not from you, it's from the enemy.

41:16.704 --> 41:23.692
And I pray that you protect the space from any of his schemes, that you protect the space from any of the lives of the enemy that would tell us otherwise.

41:24.052 --> 41:27.276
Lord Jesus, give us clarity to see you the way that you really are.

41:29.258 --> 41:32.882
Lord, I pray for all of us as a church that you would give us

41:33.570 --> 41:37.155
the mercy to continually repent and turn to you.

41:37.195 --> 41:44.845
And I pray for an abundance of fruit in our lives this year, God, as we understand more deeply what it looks like to follow you.

41:45.265 --> 41:46.146
Help us, Lord.

41:46.887 --> 41:50.652
Help us to reflect you in what we say and what we do and how we say things.

41:54.657 --> 41:57.881
And make us aware of your presence that we're not doing this alone.

41:59.824 --> 42:01.426
We're doing this with you and with each other.

42:03.426 --> 42:06.853
Jesus, we pray that you be honored and glorified even in our midst as we worship you.

42:06.873 --> 42:07.956
And we pray these things in your name.

42:08.256 --> 42:16.754
Amen.

